re. Therefore,it calls for a detailed and comprehensive approach in identification and listing of different factors governing energy efficiency in buildings in Indian context. Again only identification of barriers is not sufficient. A system needs to be adopted how these challenges or barriers can be addressed, for that some latest tools for ranking of these identified barriers needs to be adopted. Best-Worst multi-criteria decision making is used to rank the barriers. Results show economic, governmental and technological barriers as most prominent barriers among all. The results shall be of great help in decision making for effecting the improvement and development of energy efficiency measures in buildings. With the help of decision makers a roadmap is developed to help overcome these barriers over long, medium and short term respectively.},
